  "title": "Aggressive Negotiations with Luke Skywalker",
  "summary": "Aboard his freighter Trader's Envy on the outskirts of the Coruscant system, the crime lord Tyy'sun Eson holds the Jedi Padawan Ai'kani and her friend Alistair bound and collared, guarded by the one-eyed Wookiee Kyyiriiwur. Tyy'sun opens a cloaked holo-transmission to Jedi Master Luke Skywalker to bargain for the prisoners' release. He demands holocrons, training materials, and a lightsaber from the Basilica archives in exchange for returning Ai'kani, Alistair, and the captive Yejide. Luke, projecting his power across the void to rock the ship with the Force, agrees to the exchange and sets Trandosha as the meeting point. As the deal concludes, Ai'kani silently warns Luke through their bond that Tyy'sun is lying about Yejide being his daughter, vowing to expose the truth, while Tyy'sun orders the ship to jump to hyperspace.",
